				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sregan" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1386518); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1386518&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225560" alt="SRegan" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1386518)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sregan" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1386518); return false;" >SRegan</a></span> <span class="odate time_1350328602 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Oct 2012 19:16</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1589008">
									

<p>Something I've been working on for a while - I considered rewriting as a series of vignettes, but feedback on the forums and IRC persuaded me otherwise.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Spoilers</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>It's the microcosmic Foundation within <a href="/scp-1235">SCP-1235</a>. The formatting is taken from Gears' 001 proposal, which is intended to represent how the Foundation catalogued items before the Safe-Euclid-Keter system. Similarly, it doesn't use SI units. From the perspective of the microcosmos, history played out normally until March 1st 1903, when the universe vanished and was replaced by a macroverse. History following the appearance of the macroverse is obviously divergent, which I've hopefully made nods to with 'Curie devices' and similar. The last digits of the skips referenced refer to the corresponding numbers on the main list - what seems to be an area code in Gears' 001 proposal reflects wherever possible where the skips in question were found. I had good luck with them being recovered before the point of divergence until I hit 047, which is stated to have been recovered in the 1990s. For reference. I intend this to be a similar item but not necessarily the same one - it's the item they used to modify macrocosmic virii in the early 1235 containment breaches.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

