<p>Cheers. I'm trying to keep in with the 001 proposal he came from - there Hermann Keter was presumably killed by 001 in 1911; here the point of divergence is before its discovery, so he survives and the Safe-Euclid-Keter system is never adopted. The figure is actually a blurred, desaturated stock image of a lab tech reaching down through a fumigation hood, which I thought worked well with the premise.</p>

