			<div class="content" id="post-content-1589060">
									

<p>It is. I'm sort of trying to tie together a headcanon (based on &quot;From the desk of B Dark&quot; by pooryoric) whereby Dark has some sort of skip that lets him communicate with his past self, thereby turning himself into a living (and later not-so-living) paradox engine. As a consequence, even though he's dead stacks of letters from future versions of him keep turning up, but their predictions are becoming progressively less accurate as the versions of him that are still alive get further and further from the main timeline.</p>

